canonical:
  title: 景濂亭
  author: 卓光茂
  language: lzh
  text: 懶向人前強作顔水亭終日對靑山吾家嗜好與時異此地淸幽非世閒風月無私隨處足乾坤大度放予閑逍遙自適忘機裏卧看長空倦鳥還
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 景濂亭
  author: 卓光茂
  language: lzh
  text: 懶向人前強作顔。水亭終日對靑山。吾家嗜好與時異。此地淸幽非世閒。風月無私隨處足。乾坤大度放予閑。逍遙自適忘機裏。卧看長空倦鳥還。
korean:
  title: 경렴정 익재소명
  author: 탁광무
  language: kor
  text: |-
    사람들 앞에 억지 웃음 짓기 싫어
    온종일 수정에서 청산만 바라보네
    우리 집의 기호는 시속과는 다르네
    이 땅의 청한은 세상 것이 아니로세
    풍월은 사가 없으니 가는 곳마다 푸짐하고
    천지는 도량이 커서 한가한 나를 내버려두네
    만사를 다 잊고서 멋대로 거닐다가
    누워서 공중에 돌아오는 지친 새를 보노라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0190_010_0550&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Gyeongryeom Pavilion
  author: Cheok Gwang-mu
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I weary of forcing smiles before the crowd—
    At the water pavilion, all day I gaze upon green mountains.
    Our household's tastes run counter to the world's.
    This place's serenity belongs to no mortal realm.
    Wind and moonlight show no partiality, abundance wherever I turn;
    Heaven and earth possess such generous breadth, they grant me leisure.
    Wandering free, lost in forgetfulness of all schemes,
    I lie and watch the weary birds circle home through empty sky.
  footnotes:
    - The 'water pavilion' (水亭) suggests a retreat built near water, a traditional symbol of escape from worldly affairs in East Asian poetry.
    - The phrase 'wind and moonlight' (風月) represents natural beauty and poetic inspiration, classical tropes for spiritual solace.
    - '''The machine'' (機) refers to human scheming and contrivance—forgetting it represents achieving a state of natural spontaneity.'
    - The returning birds serve as a mirror for the speaker's own journey toward rest and acceptance of one's place in the natural order.
